Load the data for 2009 and past.

Pull those with placenta and the max/highest preg number in NSF study

Load 2014 women

with placenta data, plus those without but the max pregnancy in the NSF.

placenta.women <- read_csv(here::here("Output/Data", "placenta_women.csv"))
all.nsf.fem.no0preg.maxNSF <- read_csv(here::here("Output/Data", "all_nsf_fem_no0preg_maxNSF.csv"))
nsf.picks <- c(as.character(placenta.women$uncchdid), as.character(all.nsf.fem.no0preg.maxNSF$uncchdid))

nsf.picks <- nsf.picks[!duplicated(nsf.picks)]
reprostat05.nsf.selected <- reprostat05_w_pregord %>% filter(uncchdid %in% as.character(all.nsf.fem.no0preg.maxNSF$uncchdid)) %>% 
    filter(reprostat == "pregnant" | reprostat == "breastfeeding" | uncchdid %in% 
        as.character(placenta.women$uncchdid))
nsf.long.max <- read_csv(here::here("Output/Data", "preg_all_57914_long.csv"))
names(nsf.long.max)

# Find the max 'new.preg'
nsf.single.max <- nsf.long.max %>% group_by(uncchdid) %>% mutate(new.preg.term.date = ymd(paste(yearprg, 
    monthprg, dayprg, sep = "-"))) %>% select(-dayblood, -monthblood, -yearblood, 
    -monthprg, -dayprg, -yearprg) %>% slice(which.max(new.preg))

nsf.single.max.clean <- nsf.single.max %>% select(-not.it, uncchdid)

nsf.selected.w.max <- left_join(reprostat05.nsf.selected, nsf.single.max.clean, 
    by = "uncchdid")

pregord.long <- nsf.selected.w.max %>% select(uncchdid, reprostat, pregord_2005, 
    term.or.draw.date, new.preg, new.preg.term.date) %>% gather("sample", "date", 
    term.or.draw.date, new.preg.term.date) %>% gather("time", "pregs", pregord_2005, 
    new.preg) %>% arrange(uncchdid)

pregord.long.clean <- pregord.long[pregord.long$sample == "term.or.draw.date" & 
    pregord.long$time == "pregord_2005" | pregord.long$sample == "new.preg.term.date" & 
    pregord.long$time == "new.preg", ]

pregord.long.clean

pregord.long.clean$time <- factor(pregord.long.clean$time, levels = c("pregord_2005", 
    "new.preg"))

ggplot(pregord.long.clean, aes(x = time, y = pregs, color = reprostat)) + geom_line(aes(group = uncchdid), 
    size = 2, alpha = 0.5)

pregord.long.clean %>% arrange(uncchdid) %>% ggplot(., aes(x = date, y = pregs, 
    color = reprostat, group = uncchdid)) + geom_line(aes(group = uncchdid), 
    size = 1, alpha = 0.3) + scale_x_date(date_breaks = "2 year", date_labels = "%Y")

# Not sure how to get the x-axis a bit smaller so that one observations

    geom_histogram()
